    "image": "/images/new-plans-announcement.png",
    "content": "\r\nWe're excited to announce two new additions to CheckIn More: a **free plan** and a **Premium plan** — along with a new anomalous missed check-in detection feature that comes with all plans.\r\n\r\nHere's what's new and what it means for you.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## <Icon name=\"gift\" /> A Free Plan, Because Peace of Mind Shouldn't Have a Paywall\r\n\r\nCheckIn More now has a genuinely free tier. No trial period, no credit card required.\r\n\r\nThe free plan includes:\r\n- **1 daily check-in time**\r\n- **Email notifications** to 1 contact\r\n- Mood status check-ins and assistance request button\r\n\r\nWe're able to offer this for free because email is a fundamentally cheaper notification channel than SMS or phone calls — sending an email costs a fraction of a cent, while texts and calls carry real per-message costs. That difference lets us offer a useful, fully functional plan at no cost, and only charge when we're incurring costs to deliver something more.\r\n\r\nIf one daily check-in and a single contact is all you need, the free plan may be all you ever need.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## <Icon name=\"phone-call\" /> Premium Plan: Phone Calls for the Moments That Matter\r\n\r\nThe new **Premium plan** ($19.99/month) adds AI phone calls to your contacts when you miss a check-in.\r\n\r\nWhy does that matter? A missed check-in email is easy to overlook. A text is better. But a phone call is harder to miss — and for the people who care about you most, that urgency is sometimes exactly what the situation calls for.\r\n\r\nPremium plan includes everything in Plus (email + SMS notifications, unlimited check-ins, unlimited contacts), and adds:\r\n- **AI phone call to contacts** on a missed check-in\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## <Icon name=\"shield-alert\" /> New Feature: Anomalous Missed Check-in Detection\r\n\r\nAll three plans now include a new smart alerting feature: **anomalous missed check-in detection**.\r\n\r\nHere's how it works: CheckIn More learns your check-in patterns over time. If it detects an unusual number of missed check-ins — beyond what's normal for you — it can trigger an additional, escalated notification to your contacts.\r\n\r\nThis pairs naturally with the notification tiers. For example:\r\n\r\n- **Missed check-in** → SMS text to contacts\r\n- **Anomalous pattern detected** → Phone call to contacts\r\n\r\nAnd on the free plan, this means you can have a setup where email is only sent when something genuinely unusual is happening — a quiet, low-friction safety net that only speaks up when it's worth paying attention to.\r\n\r\nFor most people, a missed check-in is a forgotten phone, a late errand, or a nap that ran long. An anomalous pattern is something worth paying closer attention to. This feature helps the people who care about you tell the difference — without flooding them with alerts for every minor slip.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## <Icon name=\"layers\" /> Updated Plan Overview\r\n\r\n| | Free | Plus | Premium |\r\n|---|---|---|---|\r\n| **Price** | Free | $6.99/month | $19.99/month |\r\n| **Check-ins per day** | 1 | Unlimited | Unlimited |\r\n| **Contacts** | 1 | Unlimited | Unlimited |\r\n| **Email notifications** | <Yes /> | <Yes /> | <Yes /> |\r\n| **SMS notifications** | <No /> | <Yes /> | <Yes /> |\r\n| **AI phone calls** | <No /> | <No /> | <Yes /> |\r\n| **Anomalous missed check-in detection** | <Yes /> | <Yes /> | <Yes /> |\r\n| **Mood status & assistance request** | <Yes /> | <Yes /> | <Yes /> |\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nWe built CheckIn More because we believe a simple daily check-in is one of the most meaningful things you can do for the people who care about you. These new plans — and the new detection feature — are steps toward making that as accessible and as reliable as possible.\r\n\r\nAs always, if you have feedback or questions, you're reaching the founders directly.\r\n\r\n<DownloadButtons slug=\"new-plans-announcement\" />\r\n",
